ITAL OPTICAL RECORDING, PRINCIPLES AND POSSIBLE APPLICATIONS.     DIGITAL OPTICAL RECORDING IS A NEW TECHNOLOGY BASED ON THE CAPABILITIES OF ADIODE LASER TO MELT HOLES IN A TELLURIUM LAYER. 25,000 PAGES CAN BE WRITTENONTO A DOR DISC. A SET OF DOR DISCS CAN FORM THE BACKBONE OF AN ELECTRONICDOCUMENT STORAGE SYSTEM WHICH CAN BE APPLIED IN VARIOUS ARCHIVAL APPLICATIONS